               <msContents class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh2008115302">
                  <summary>1 copy of Mirʾāt-i Sikandarī by Sikandar ibn Mu'hammad ʿArab Manjhū ibn Akbar</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_RSPA_8-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="274v"/>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_3838">Mirʾāt-i Sikandarī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_3838">مرآت سکندر</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>The gap in the explicit represents where a word has been almost entirely efface because of repair tape. The only letter which remains visible is a final tā. </p>
                     </note>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">الحمد لله الذی جعل فردا من افراد البشر</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">که بسیاری بوقت صبح یکدعا بکند __ت تمام شد تواریخ کجرات</explicit>
                     <decoNote/>
                     <author>
